INSERT INTO `group_all_post` VALUES('1','I AM A WINNER!','admin','Wednesday: 2001-01-03 ','../default/thumbanon.jpg','04:03:04 AM','1537087458','0','Super Administrator','post','none','a61e4095bfeab58','eb0d278c1feafab');
INSERT INTO `group_all_post` VALUES('2','Home \ncurriculum\n\n\n\nCONTENTS\nYOU HAVE A BRAIN\nPARENTAL INFLUENCE\nPOWERING THE BRAIN\nADOPT A POSITIVE MENTAL ATTITUDE\nUNFAIR ADVANTAGE\nEXTRAL POINTS\n\n\n\n\nDEDICATION\nTo my mother to whom I shall remain indebted for setting the foundation on which this book is based.\n\n\n\n\n\nACKNOWLEDGEMENT \nAny accomplishment requires the effort of many people and this book is not different.\nI am also giving my grateful acknowledgement to&hellip;&hellip;\nIndeed cooperation is the key to success. Thank you (name) you are still my valued friend and favoured memory.\n\n\n\n\n\nINTRODUCTION\nThomas Edison proposed that; &ldquo;The most necessary task of civilization is to teach people how to think. It should be the primary purpose of our public schools. The mind of a child is naturally active, it develops through exercises. Give a child plenty of exercise for the body and brain, and you will be amazed at the end result.\n	The trouble with our way of education is that it does not give elasticity to the mind. It cast the brain into a mold, it insist that the child must accept. It does not encourage original thought or reasoning and it lays more stress on memory than observation&rdquo;.\nI have been making the list of things they don&amp;amp;#39;t teach in schools which should have been part of our school curriculum. This is one of them; Training the Brain.\n	This is beyond the fault of a class teacher. It is just that, our school curriculum was not designed to teach children to think for themselves. In actuality, our current school system is based on a Prussian Model that was developed to do just the opposite - to teach children to obey orders and do as they are told. But the good news is that, education is a team endeavour. The teachers, parents, students and the community are all members of this team. If one member is not involved, the students education will suffer.\nI Father Livingproof (A Brain Coach) therefore come as a member of the community through this construction manual to join hands with the parents and teachers to train your child&rsquo;s greatest gift so that they will not become a liability to the society. It is on this note I welcome you to this training field.\nThis is HOME CURRICULUM.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nREALITY\nThe biggest atrocity of all is to indoctrinate our children into a system that does not value their creative expression or encourage their unique abilities.\nThe human brain is the warehouse of creative power.\nThe best predictor of smart children is smart parents.\nThe &ldquo;curriculum of family&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; is at the heart of any good life. We have gotten away from that curriculum - it&amp;amp;#39;s time to return to it.\nWhen a national leaders set educational policies, it should be with the intention to achieve the purpose and the talents he has and to help all persons become wholesome human being.\nSchool changes too slowly and the world is changing too rapidly. But your child can only meet up by your attention to the development of their brain.\n When children are respected, they are respectful.\n    Nations are made from the classroom.\n\n\n\n                          YOU HAVE A BRAIN\n   So You Want To Raise Smart Kids? Of course you do! Every parent wants the best for their child. But you might ask; how do I go about it? \n   My goal is to bring you early childhood activities while spending quality time with your kids and optimally stimulating their brain.\nYes, your child&amp;amp;#39;s baby brain development can be improved by you. Whatever the age, you can develop your child&rsquo;s brainpower.\nYou must understand that babies are one of nature&amp;amp;#39;s most perfect learning machines. Starting early in your baby&amp;amp;#39;s brain development can do wonder for their mental growth in later year, and give them a large head start over their age mates. \nTHE AMAZING BRAIN\nI wonder if you really have an understanding on how amazing and remarkable is the human brain in you and your child&rsquo;s skull.\nInside each human brain are approximately 86 billion neurons interconnected by more than 100 trillion synapses (this is just an estimation since no one has counted them yet), which science has only barely began to understand. And 16 billion in our cerebral cornet alone, Human brain start developing immediately after conception. The body of a mother began creating neurons at the rate of about 400 million per day during the first month of pregnancy.\nYour brains generate electricity constantly. So when you say; &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;that&amp;amp;#39;s a bright idea&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;, your statement could be literally as well as figuratively true.\n   When scientists try to quantify the capacity of the brain, the number gets so high that we can&amp;amp;#39;t get our minds around them. The potential of our mind is literally mindboggling.\nI marvel at the mystery of human brain each time I think about it. This is what makes us different from each other in millions of ways. This is what holds our memories, all our thoughts and all our dreams.\nDo you realize that no super computer on earth can come near to the capacity of the average human brain? The most complex organ system in the entire universe is a tremendous gift from God.\nThe brain sorts, organizes and ware-houses that huge of sensory data streaming in at million of bytes per second.\nIt is the control and command centre for all our senses, all our other organs, our body temperature and operation of every system in the human body. \nThe brain also enables us to imagine, to create and to solve problems.\nA human brain comes programmed with the ability to extract information from the past, gather information from the present, and integrate that data and project it into the future which means, we&amp;amp;#39;re the only creature on earth with the capacity to analyze, strategize and prioritize so as to alter and improve the world around us.\nI am giving you these details so that you can appreciate the most tremendous gift from God to human beings.\n\nLEFT AND RIGHT BRAIN\nYou may have heard some people bragging about their math skills and some touting their creativity. That&amp;amp;#39;s to let you know that the brain is divided into two hemispheres down the middle with each half performing distinct set of operations. \nThe human brain hemisphere operates in concert with each other and independently. The thick Corpus Callosum that connects the two hemispheres enables them to communicate information to each other. The right brain hemisphere controls the muscles on the right side of the human body.\nFor instance, when you wink your left eye, that&amp;amp;#39;s the right side of your brain at work, and when you wink your right eye, that&amp;amp;#39;s the left side of your brain at work. This is made happened because of the criss-cross wiring nature of the brain hemisphere.\nGenerally, the use of the two sections of the brain is far more complex than just a single individual.\nThe right hemisphere is mainly in charge of spatial abilities, face recognition and processing music. It helps us to comprehend visual imagery and make sense of what we see. It plays a role in language and interpreting a person&amp;amp;#39;s tone.\nWhile the left hemisphere is dominant in language: processing what you hear and handling most of the duties of speaking.\nWhen you need to retrieve a fact, your left brain pulls it from your memory.\nThough, right-brain is often regarded as more &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;creative&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;, there is no right or wrong here; It is merely two different ways of thinking. One is not better than the other, just as being right-handed is not &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;superior&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; to being left-handed. What is important is for us to know that there are different ways of thinking, and by knowing what your natural preference is, you can pay attention to your less dominant side to improve the same.\nChildren can fully realize their potential by activating both sides of their brain, we can be more creative.\nMore so, because left brain strategies are the ones used most often in the classroom, right brain students sometime feel neglected (i.e. left-handed students).\nThe left brain is often called Digital Brain. It controls reading and writing. While the Right brain is referred to as the Analog Brain. It controls three-dimensional sense, creativity and artistic senses. These two together allows us to function as human.\nStrengthened brain will enable your child to be more successful academically, become better able to cope with life&amp;amp;#39;s daily challenges and improve their ability to relate with others.\nNOTE\nThere is no difference between male and female&amp;amp;#39;s brain. It is the same make-up. \nIt is the same content all over the world. No difference between a white man&rsquo;s brain and a black man&rsquo;s own. Often different set of people talked about it to my hearing. They even argue about the margin and the magnitude of the differences. But the truth is that, there is no difference in our brain content. Whatever difference you have noticed is due to individual&rsquo;s usage. They accepted responsibility to improve and maximize their brain. And they created a favourable environment for themselves.\nParents can as well make their immediate environment conducive enough for their children think better and improve on their brain. There is no barrier to the improvement of one&rsquo;s brain. It is all about commitment and dedication to the activities that will help improve it. That&rsquo;s all....\n\n  \n                                          CHAPTER 2\n                              PARENTAL INFLUENCE \nThe impact of failure can cause lasting damage to self-esteem and the consequences can influence an entire lifetime.\nIn studying the complexities of the failure problem, I have come up with what I believe could be