ric and invented things that have changed the world. He invented electric bulb and motion picture camera and many other things. That was why Thomas Edison proposed that; &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;The most necessary task of civilization is to teach people how to think. It should be the primary purpose of our schools&hellip;&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;.\nCome to think of it, if the mother had not taken the responsibility to train the child by herself, imagine what would have become of Thomas Edison. I believe his name would not have been stencilled on the mental sheet of history.\n There is this story of a young African American man that millions of people including me find inspiration and encouragement in his life. He was born into poverty, abandoned by his father and raised by his mother.\nThis young man was tagged the dummy of his fifth-grade class. But wherever and whenever this young man share his story, he is found of crediting his mother as the single most important human influence on his life. The name of this young man is Ben Carson. This man whom everybody in his class at the fifth-grade felt he could not amount to anything good eventually became a brain surgeon and head of paediatric neurosurgery at one of the most respected medical training institutes in the world.\nHis mother Sonya Carson became his greatest inspiration and provided the foundation for everything he has ever accomplished during his life. He said the mother shaped the heart of whom he is and taught him eternal truths by demonstrating exceptional character.\nThese two stories you just read have similarities. And one of the major similarities is the parental influence.\nParental influence in building and developing kid&rsquo;s brain cannot be over emphasised.\nIt is one assignment that you must be committed to and give your total attention to it. It needs your full involvement.\nYou might be saying that what is now the school&rsquo;s assignment if they can&amp;amp;#39;t do these? After all, I am paying a huge amount of money for school fees.\nYes! That is true. You are absolutely right. But the &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;better truth&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; is that, to train your child&amp;amp;#39;s brain is not inherent in school design. It is absolutely Home curriculum.\nSome teachers are tremendously fantastic. I can&amp;amp;#39;t dispute that fact. But no matter how fantastically they might be, they are &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;strangers&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. This is one of the highest/greatest mistakes from many parents. They entrust the destiny of their kids in the hands of a &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;stranger&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. They expect these teachers to help them in their responsibilities. Whereas, these teachers work with an order.\nThey have scheme of work and curriculum that they follow strictly. Any attempt to deviate put their work on risk.\nYou also need to know that, both the parents and the teachers are victims of the same dwarfed educational system.\nThat means you need extra curriculum to exempt your kids from these woes.\nSchooling have been restricted to just facts and figures which shouldn&amp;amp;#39;t be. It should be a system where kids are taught how to think independently so that their creative skills can be developed.\nListen to me, I have scanned and x-ray our educational system, I know what it lacks.\nR. Buckminster Fuller said; &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;Everyone is born a Genius, But the process of life de-geniuses them&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. Our educational system is failing. It is not preparing children for the real world. Though, they may not admit to that. But that is the truth.\nAnd our kids are our only hope for Africa&amp;amp;#39;s future, just as we the parents are their only hope for the present and immediate future.\nIt is on this premise I dare to challenge every parent to begin to create special time for their kid&rsquo;s brain development. Intelligence is 49% genetic and 51% stimulation says