&amp;amp;#39;s mood per time, you won&amp;amp;#39;t know what to do to strengthen him/her.\nNaturally babies are designed to learn. That&amp;amp;#39;s why they are very inquisitive. It is an inbuilt thing. It is inherent in them. Every child is always curious to know everything they see. And it&amp;amp;#39;s our assignment as a parent to work on that curiosity not to die down. This is a universal trait in kids. But we still have some that possess some unique character. There are some commonly recognized characteristics like;\nCholeric: adventurous, determined, outspoken, competitive, strong-willed\nSanguine: playful, sociable, talkative, lively, imaginative\nMelancholy: detailed, orderly, persistent, respectful, deep\nPhlegmatic: thoughtful, controlled, adaptable, attentive, diplomatic\nWhether or not, these terms are familiar to you. You have probably intuited a lot about your child&amp;amp;#39;s personality type just by noticing his everyday reactions and motivations.\nGeneral characteristics of children\nLove stories and have a rich imagination\nWant good to triumph over evil\nEnjoying singing, acting and being creative\nAre generally carefree\nAre emotionally sensitive\nForgive easily and forget quickly\nCan easily become discouraged\nAre good at memorizing\nAre eager to learn and acquire skills\nAre trusting and believe what adults tell them\nUnderstanding all this characteristics will give you a clear road map on how you can relate with them.\nLEFT-RIGHT BRAIN CONNECTION.\nMany theories have proven the differences between the left and right hemisphere of human brain. They are responsible for different functions. It has been proved that the left brain is responsible for analysis, while the right brain is the creative one. The left brain is also responsible for language skills, while the right brain is responsible for &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; thinking in pictures&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. It has been proven that the two can be fortified. And that is called; &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;WHOLE BRAIN THINKING&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;.\nThe techniques to strengthen the connection between the right brain and the left brain include everything that has to do with the &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; Cross pattern Coordination&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; movement. \nFor instance, babies practice this when they start crawling. The left brain arm comes forward while the right leg comes forward and then in turn the right arm and the left leg comes forward.\nThis cross movement contributes to the development of the connection between the two hemispheres of the brain. This cross pattern also happens in normal walking. Walking is a very healthy and beneficiary activity. But most parents restrict their kids from moving around, jumping, shouting, and so on. All these activities work wonders in the brain. \n Another activity that only few people know about and that proves to be extremely effective is practicing writing with the non-dominant hand.\nA right handed child should practice using left hand in writing and the left handed child should practice using right hand in writing. This will benefit your child tremendously.\nDrumming is another beneficial activity that helps strengthen the connection between the right and left brain. It also helps a child in the recognition and memorizing of patterns. The truth is, you can stimulate both sides of the brain to stay balanced. \nThe right and left sides of the brain focus on different skills which when combined, enables individual to be rational and spontaneous, analytical and creative. As with physical exercise, working on both sides of the brain enables them to sharpen and coordinate. As I have said earlier, the right brain is associated with creativity. \nMost people love to be more creative. You may feel that you have an untapped talent or creative ability, but you&amp;amp;#39;re not sure what it is. The right hemisphere of your brain is considered to be your creative centre. Activities such as music, art and using your imagination are generally thought of as right brain activities.\nYou can stimulate your child creativity and imagination and maximize you productivity, through specific right brain focused exercise.\n	To strengthen the right brain, make your kids listen to a guided visualization and meditation program.\nAn intimate program to free the power of their imagination. We are more receptive to right- brain insights when we are relaxed.\n	Sing or learn to play an instrument like piano, listening to or performing music helps to stimulate the auditory cortex of the right-brain and leads to increased creativity.\n	Encourage drawing, sketching or even tracing a picture can encourage your right brain to become more active. Hands-on, visually focused artistic activities such as sculpting or drawing promote right brain activity.\nAs for the left brain, since it is responsible for mental activities like, logic, analysis, speech and language. Using the right side of your body stimulates the left-brain. When you try to solve a word puzzle for example, electrical and chemical impulses travel among the neurons in the left hemisphere until you identify the answer. Games like Sudoku and crossword puzzles, logic brain teasers and mathematical word problem, all exercise the left side of the brain. \nExercising the right side of the body wakes up the left side of your brain. Even writing with your right hand is helpful.\nAlso, single nostril breath stimulates the left side of the brain. For this practice, block your left nostril and inhale through the right nostril and then block your right nostril and inhale through the left for a few circles.\nNote, children with dominant right-brain may &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;struggle&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; academically in a traditional classroom environment. The struggle in memorizing fact and paying attention to details\nThey tend to be disorganized and have difficulty focusing for any length of time. They often don&rsquo;t perform well in school and parents may become so discouraged. \nYou may also find that your right brained child has problems with memorizing lists or tables, has difficulty understanding verbal instructions, struggles with writing, cannot focus on one task for too long and generally doesn&amp;amp;#39;t enjoy school.\nIt is not their fault. I told you that I have x-ray our traditional school curriculum and I know exactly what it lacks.\nModern educational systems are developed mainly for left-brained children, who like to structure, plan, work alone and solve problems with logic. That is the reason why the right-brained children finds it difficult  to settle into school routines and often need assistance in order to cope successfully with the challenges of scholastic life.  \nRIGHT BRAIN LEARNING STRATEGIES\nBecause a right-brained child can often find it difficult to memorize facts with auditory cues such as repetition or rhymes, a good idea is to provide visual cues like picture stories which appeal to the emotions like blocks or coloured counters. They respond well to visual demonstrations on PowerPoint and enjoy music, videos and dance as methods of learning.\nThey prefer to;\nDraw rather than write\nBe shown rather than told how to do a task\nPhysically handle objects\nSolve problems by working at similarities and patterns\nAssimilate whole chunks of information rather than break them down into discrete facts. (3). THE OXYGEN WE BREATH\nThe amount of oxygen we get into our brain is a significant factor in brain development. Children used to spend their time outside, in the fresh air, run around, play ball and other games, jump rope, yell and scream while playing. All this makes the lungs to be filled with loads of fresh air. But nowadays, many of the children spend more and more hours sitting in front of TV or in front of their computers playing games, surfing the internet or simply doing their homework.\nA good balance between exercise and studying is recommended for healthy brain development. All exercise and sport games develop good coordination, lung capacity and a strong body. But there are some specific activities that prove to be especially beneficial for the children of today.\nSwimming is one of the most beneficial activities. It has been proven to be a superior exercise for all ages, infants to adults. Swimming is an activity that improves lung capacity and capacity of blood vessels to the brain.\nYou may not necessarily go to swimming pool. Mere immersion of your body in water to the neck level increases the delivery of blood within the brain.\nThe brain uses about three times as much oxygen as the muscles do. There are a number of different methods you can use to increase the amount of oxygen- rich blood that flows to your brain. You can consider any of the following for your kids.\nAerobic Activity: This is physical activities that causes you to breathe harder and raises your heart rate. E.g. bicycling, dancing, jumping, running, etc\nStretching during the day e.g touching your knees or toes from a standing position.\nDo yoga- yoga poses often encourage putting the head below the heart. This directly benefits blood flow to the brain.\nGive your child more chocolate. Studies suggest that the flavonoids found in cocoa beans may increase blood flow to the brain.\nDrink beet juice\nInclude &amp;amp;#34;Superfoods&amp;amp;#34; in their daily diet. E.g Nuts, seed, blueberries. \nNote, When going into swimming exercise, ensure you adhere to swimming rules and regulations in other to avoid been drown.\n4.   The power of parents\n	Talk, Talk, Talk\n	As a parent, always ask your kids an open - ended question. E. g why is the day different from the night? Why is there male and female gender? Such questions help a child reflect on what he/she knows. Don&amp;amp;#39;t worry of he/she is too young to understand.\nYou can also ask a question like this, why is the sky blue? What is the difference between sweat and tears? These kinds of questions help your child to be opened up to the wonders of the world. Parents should always share their work experience with their children. Expose your kids to images of success by taking them to work. Let them see you engaged in meaningful activities and allow them to become involved. Think of your home as a learning place. The kitchen is great for teaching math and science through cooking.\nRead, Read, Read \nResearch has repeatedly revealed that access to books and one-on-one reading time is a predictor of school success. &amp;amp;#34;Reading stimulates the brain to make connections and builds background knowledge about the world&amp;amp;#34;, say Kim Daveport, chief program officer at Jumpstart, a national early- literacy organisation.\nModelling good reading habits may give your kids an edge. And seeing his parent reading for enjoyment will be contagious.\nAlways share what you are reading with your child and let him do the same.\nThis will not only spark conversation but builds his vocabulary and comprehension.\nPaediatricians often recommend parents routinely read aloud to their young kids. It helps preschoolers brain in mental imagery and understanding narrative-both of which are key for the development of language and literacy.\nParent who spend time reading to their children create nurturing relationships, which is important for a child cognitive, language and social - emotional development. What reading does to the brain is truly fascinating.\nReading takes one to an imaginary land, faster understanding of different cultures and let you live lives you couldn&amp;amp;#39;t in the real world. When a child read a book, it becomes part of their identity.\nWhen you go out with kids for shopping, take books along. Take book to your on long trips and places where you have to wait like the doctor&amp;amp;#39;s office, motor park and air-port. Parents should have a family library day.\nWhat to Read\n   Books for kids should have simple, repetitive text and clear pictures. During the first few months of life, your child just like to hear your voice, so you can read almost anything, especially books with a sing-song or rhyming text. As your baby gets more interested in looking at things, choose books with simple pictures against solid backgrounds. Once your baby begins to grab, you can read cloth books that has faces, bright colours and shapes. When your baby begins to respond to what&amp;amp;#39;s inside of books, add board books with pictures of babies or familiar objects like toys. When your baby begins to do things like sit up in the bathtub or eat finger foods, find simple stories about daily routines like bedtime or bath time. When your baby starts talking, choose books that invite babies to repeat simple words or phrases.\n  Books with mirrors and different textures are also great for this age group, as are fold-out books that can be propped up, or books with flab&amp;amp;#39;s that open for a surprise. One of the best ways you can ensure that your little one grows up to be a reader is to have books around your house. When your baby is old enough to crawl over to a basket of toys and pick one out, make sure some books are included in the mix.\n5. BRAIN FOOD \nYour brain is always &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;on&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. It takes care of your thoughts, movement, your breathings, your heartbeat and your senses. The brain works 24/7, even while you are sleeping. This means your brain requires a constant supply of fuel. And the &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;fuel&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; comes from the foods we eat- and what is in the food makes all the difference. So, we can simply say, what you eat directly affects the structure and function of your brain.\nLike an expensive car. Your brain functions best when it gets only premium fuel.\nEating high quality foods that contain lots of vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants nourishes the brain and protect it from oxidative stress.\nHOW TO BUILD A HEALTHY BRAIN\n1. Balanced Blood Sugar\n2. Ensure Essential Fats\n3. Vitamins and Minerals\n4. Avoids Anti- nutrient and eliminate allergies.\nBALANCED BLOOD SUGAR\nSugar is your brains super fuel. But you have to make sure your child is getting the RIHGT TYPE and RIGHT AMOUNT at the RIGHT TIME.\nToo much &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;fast&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; sugar makes a blood sugar high and hyperactivity. The excess sugar in the blood gets dumped into storage as abdominal fat. Eating little and often helps keep your child&amp;amp;#39;s energy and concentration even. \nHOW TO BALANCE BLOOD SUGAR\nGo for food with slow releasing sugars. E.g. Oats, Brown Rice, Brown Bread, Whole Wheat Pasta, vegetables (Excluding Potatoes). Eat three meals and two snacks a day. This will help to maintain your child&amp;amp;#39;s sugar level and prevent highs and lows. \nCombine protein with carbohydrate. Protein slows down the absorption of sugar found in carbohydrates. E.g. mackerel and toast with egg. \nENSURE ESSENTIAL FATS\nWhy is a fat head a smart head? 60% of a dried brain weight is fat. It is no wonder deficiencies in specific kinds of fats can have huge repercussions on intelligence and behaviour. If your child is having 3 portions of oily fish and a daily portion of seeds, they should be getting a good level to help their brains develop and boost IQ.\nTo give your child all the essential fat they need, give them plenty of seeds and nuts. You can grind and sprinkle them on cereal, soups and selects.\nAvoid deep fried, browned and processed foods.\nVITAMINS AND MINERALS\nVitamins and Mineral are intelligent nutrient that keep the brain in tune. They are key to building and rebuilding the brain. They mainly come from fruits, vegetables and whole food, and can be supplemented for optimum brain performance e.g. berries, apples, grapes, spinach etc. \nAVOID ANTI-NUTRIENTS AND ELIMINATE FOOD ALLERGIES\nThere are some foods that rob your child&amp;amp;#39;s brain of nutrients. Such foods are; \nRefined sugar: These are essentially carbohydrate robbed of essential nutrients.\nDamaged Fats: These Comes From Fried Foods and Hydrogenated Fats. \nChemical Food Additives Another healthy group of brain food contains omega-3 fatty acids. Omega-3s help improve general brain functioning and restore memory. Brain food high in Omega-3 Includes; salmon, mackerel, sardines, and Warnuts.\nIn conclusion, nutrition directly affects your child&amp;amp;#39;s\nIQ\nLearning \nConcentration \nBehaviour\nSleep\n\n\n\n\n\n\n                                         CHAPTER 4\n                        ADOPT A POSITIVE MENTAL ATTITUDE\nWhat determines a man speed limit in life is the man&amp;amp;#39;s attitude towards life. William James of Harvard University said; &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;The greatest discovery of my generation is that human being can alter their lives by altering their attitudes of mind&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. It is therefore a matter of urgency for parents to start building a positive mental attitude in their children early in their lives.\nATTITUDE is the most important word in English Language. And it is the formation of success. It is absolutely impossible for any child to become outstanding in life without a positive mental attitude. Teach your kids how to see themselves as an important person. Let them know there is no gender difference in the school of success. Often celebrate your child. Continually delete from their memory the negative feelings of failure, depression, defeat and the feeling of giving up.\n&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;There was a man who made his living selling balloons at a fair. He had balloons of many different colours, including red, yellow, blue and green. Whenever business was slow, he would release a helium-filled balloon into the air. When the children saw balloon group, they all wanted one. They would come up to him, buy a balloon and his sales would go up again. All day, he continued to release a balloon whenever the sales go down. One day, the balloon man felt someone tugging at his jacket. He turned around and a little boy asked, &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;If you release a black balloon, would that also fly&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;? Moved by the boy&amp;amp;#39;s concern, the man replied gently, &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;son, it is not the colour of the balloon, it is what is inside that makes it go up.&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; Extracted from YOU CAN WIN by SHIV KHERA.\nWhat is the moral of this story? So many people associate their failures to gender or race difference not knowing that success does not have a destination or favourite. Let your child know that just anybody can make it in life. Instil in your child ethics of achievement.\nThe words you say to them, the confidence you build in them, and the opportunity you offer them to practice resilience can make a big difference-to their long-term development. Helping your children develop a positive mental attitude will contribute greatly to their well-being.\nAs Zig-Zaglar statement; we have within us everything we need to have a happy and meaningful life. Developing a positive mental attitude is a great way to keep the sun shining and help those seeds blossom into success.\nI strongly believe that one of the greatest gifts our creator gave us is the ability to choose our thoughts. It is true that we can&amp;amp;#39;t always help what we think, but we can choose what we dwell on and how we respond-our attitude.\nParents can help their kids learn how to choose the positive thoughts over the negative thoughts, and create a positive mental attitude that will help them find happiness and success. We can teach them to deposit the good thoughts into their brain (as if it&amp;amp;#39;s a bank account) and discard the rest. This is called Emotional control-our ability to control our emotions, as opposed to letting them control us. Though we may face some challenges with our positive mental attitude, and the world around us will knock us down a little. But by teaching our kids how to take the fall, we can help them get back up and try again with a smile on their face and a spring in their step.\nShow your kids how to look for the good in everything instead of the bad aspect of things. Even hard situations probably have some sort of positive message or lesson hidden inside somewhere.\n                                      CHAPTER 5\n                                    UNFAIR ADVANTAGE\nUnfair advantage changed the rules and the intent of schooling thereby affecting the performance of our children. Gone are the days where teachers are blamed for the poor academic performance of our kids. The unfair advantage has changed the rules.\nDr. David .O. Oyedepo said; &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;Performance is not an issue of teachers as it were, it&amp;amp;#39;s an issue of students; it all depends on their interest and commitment&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;.\nAs a parent, you need to know that whatever your child becomes in life is still part of your responsibilities.\nThe governmental policies do not favour everybody. And the masses are the victims. We operate an institution that favours just the few elites. That is why I said, it is an unfair advantage.\nPlease, just carefully follow me because you will be exposed to some hidden facts about our schooling system.\nThe children of this few elite that the operated institution favours does not receive the kind of education that the masses receives.\nFor instance, our school system is designed to indoctrinate children into a system that does not value their creative expression nor encourage their unique abilities. These I consider the biggest and the mother of all atrocities.\nBut the children of these few elites go to a school that is so specific about what they want to become in life. While the majority cannot afford to pay the bills for such schools. Is this not an unfair Advantage?\nAs a matter of recorded facts, when a nation does not operate an inclusive political and economic institution, the masses suffer the brunt. They tend to make policies that favour just the narrow elites. And this does not exclude educational policy.\nImagine, our nation Nigeria still remains comparatively underdeveloped after several decades of obtaining flag-independence. Is this not a matter of great regret and concern?\nTaylor Gatto said; &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;To entrust government with the power of determining education which our children shall receive is entrusting our servants with the power of the master&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. That is why there is still legal basis of injustice in our educational system.\nNigeria is a catalogue of penal legislation. Some of the political leaders are savvy. They said we are in a democratic season. But our politicians do not see the government of the people for the people. They are slayers of democracy. That is why they will never democratize quality education. But as a parent or whatever, you must make yourself a life student and inject the same into your kids. \nWe must never mistaking schooling for education. It is possible to spend six years in school and still not be educated. Don&rsquo;t be deceived, our schooling system is preparing our kids for the future that don&rsquo;t exist. What is imbedded in the school curriculum is different from what you will meet in the said future. That is a curriculum of confusion not education. The things taught in schools and colleges are not education but a means to an education.\nFor this reason you need to liberate yourself and your kids from the shackles of ignorance. Rather than preparing your kids for the future according to the school curriculum, you can prepare the future for your kids. That is what all the few elites do for their kids. Remember ignorance can destroy life at an unimaginable proportion. Get yourself educated and you will be empowered to do the same for your kids.\nWe need to know this fact too. Our schools inability to educate our kids is not the fault of any teacher or too little money spent. It is inherent in the design of the thing. It&amp;amp;#39;s just impossible for education and schooling ever to be the same thing. Any kind of education that takes the will from the people is not education but schooling.\nSchool has become too vital a jobs project and a protector of the social order to allow itself to be &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;re-formed&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. It has political allies to guard its marches. That is why reforms comes and go without changing much. \nSo if a nation expects to be ignorant and free in a state of civilization, it expects what never was and will never be.\nIndira Gandhi, a former prime minister of India said; &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;Education is a liberating force and in our age, it is also a democratising force, cutting across the barriers of castes and class, smoothing out inequalities imposed by birth and other circumstances&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. But what we are experiencing is quite different from what it should be. And if we don&amp;amp;#39;t wake up as a nation or as an individual to start taking responsibility to building our educational system, we are in for a train wreck of catastrophic portions. \nThis is a collective responsibility by individual committing to developing yourself, kids and your immediate environment. This is what I call government. \nRemember I said, our kids are the only hope of Africa. And as a parent we must not fail to do the necessity.\nYou must create a conducive environment for the development of your kids. Don&amp;amp;#39;t put all your hope in school. Home school your children. The school change too slowly and the world is changing too rapidly.\nThe current school curriculum is still trapped in the tar pit of industrial age. The curriculum is not current. It is outdated. It is not meeting up with the current situations in the world. So we are living behind the time. The knowledge the school Curriculum is dishing out cannot solve our current problem. &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;Analog knowledge&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39; can never solve &amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;Digital problem&amp;amp;#39;&amp;amp;#39;. They are too opposite. Our traditional schools are only interested in grades and credentials but what you need in a real life is personal development courses that will enhance your operational skills without grading.\nTherefore, I beseech you, the destiny of our nation must not be truncated. If our parents failed us, we must not fail our own children. We must be committed to building the builders. And now is the time.','admin','Wednesday: 2001-01-03 ','../default/thumbanon.jpg','04:09:55 AM','1537088458','0','Super Administrator','post','none','f046e89202ce1d0','eb0d278c1feafab');
