INSERT INTO `group_all_post` VALUES('4','SCHOOL PROFILE\nWise virgin Nursery and Basic School came into being in April 2005. The Proprietor and Proprietress; Mr. and Mrs. Boluwatife are professional teachers who were inspired by God (using human vessel) to establish a school that will inculcate Godly values into the lives of children.\nEver since the establishment of the school, in the year 2005, the management and teachers have not stopped giving good and qualitative education to their pupils. The guiding principle to attain this excellent height is embedded in the school Mission statement.\nA CHRIST CENTRED School dedicated to a vision of bringing up academically, intellectually, emotionally and spiritually sound children.\nThis vision has made wisevirgin school a pacesetter in the educational sector.\nWise virgin is GOVERNMENT APPROVED and is registered with the corporate affairs commission.\nWISE VIRGIN COLLEGE Was given birth to in the year 2012. Those first set of students are now (Sept. 2017) in SSS III.\n	To talk about our performances, without collecting money from parents, the school on its own do registered 10 students (5 Junior and 5 Seniors) annually for Olympiad competition organized by Mathematical centre Abuja. When the result of the first round of 2017 was released, one of our students had second best result in Chemistry and was invited to Lokoja for second round.\n	Again, the school registered 10 students (5Junior and 5 Seniors) annually for Cowbell Mathematic Quiz Competition called Cowbellpedia.\n	Hon. Prince Yomi Kolawole (then Majority Leader and now Speaker) in the Kogi State House of Assembly organized a quiz Competition for all Secondary School in Kabba/Bunu L. G. A. in 2017. Close to 40 Secondary Schools were invited. Wise Virgin was represented by 1 student in SSS 2 and another from SSS 1. Since we had no SSS 3 then. In the first round. Wisevirgin faced Christ Anglican Secondary School, Kabba and won them with 8 points. In the second round, we faced Sacred Heart College Kabba and again by God&rsquo;s grace won them too with 8 points.\n	We did not do badly seeing that we have no SSS 3 students yet. Our SSS 1 and 2 competed and won Schools that have SSS 3. We thank God and promise to do better now that we have reached SSS 3.\n	Also, one of our students (Baiyegunhi Kehinde) was best SSS 1 student during September 2016 T. J. Yusuf lesson and was given scholarship. A year later, he again came out victoriously best for SSS 2 in the same September lesson. Note Baiyegunhi Kehinde started his JSS 1 in Wisevirgin College until now he is in SSS 2.','admin','Wednesday: 2001-01-03 ','../default/thumbanon.jpg','04:13:41 AM','1537090458','0','Super Administrator','post','none','3eeae20f864a6d0','fbf1a5daeab7f23');
